I don't remember who it was, but someone made a good arguement about satanism, about there not being a line in the sand.<br>
<br>
I agree, Satanism isn't a religion I myself would chose to follow. Egoism isn't either for that matter, belive it or not those that know me don't consider me to be a egoist.<br>
<br>
I'm simply trying to say that I respect all firm beliefs in a religion, no matter the religion. <br>
<br>
The reason I've been &quot;patting the backs&quot; of satanists and egoists in this thread is that there is no satanist or egoist here to speak up for themselves.<br>
<br>
Most Christians aren't &quot;christians all the way&quot; most satanists aren't satanists all the way either. And to think of it - both are based on each other. Without heaven there is no hell, without hell there is no heaven.<br>
<br>
